<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-673-465  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 673 465.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  Dec 10 1990 v7 n49 p41(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Page scanner version of OCR software available. (Computer AidedTechnology Inc. introduces CAT Reader Professional opticalcharacter recognition software) (product announcement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Computer Aided Technology Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   CAT Reader Professional (Scanning software) (Productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionOptical Character Recognition SoftwareSoftware packages.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Computer Aided Technology Inc., a maker of hand-held scanner software,recently introduced a page scanner version of its optical characterrecognition software.andM;Called CAT Reader Professional, the program is designed to allow users toselect specific parts of the page to be scanned to speed up the processing ofsimilarly laid-out pages.andM;The program is capable of &quot;learning&quot; new type styles but it is pretrained torecognize such commonly used fonts as Courier, Helvetica and Times Roman,according to company officials.andM;The $495 software includes a spelling checker and text editor.andP;  Text can beoutput in WordPerfect, WordStar, Microsoft Word and ASCII formats.andM;The company also introduced an adapter that lets users connect popularhand-held scanners to a laptop's parallel port.andP;  Called CAT ScanAdapter LPT,the adapter works with scanners such as Logitech Inc.'s ScanMan.andP;  TheScanAdapter is priced at $149 and is available now.andM;Computer Aided Technology, of Dallas, can be reached at (214) 350-0888.andO;</TEXT></DOC>